data.text: By repurposing these jackets, the Soggy No-More project aims to create value from waste materials and reduce the disposal of non-biodegradable materials from landfills.

The collection is made by Nazanin, a social enterprise of Afghan refugees in Kuala Lumpur and it’s an exclusive Destination GOOD label of lifestyle accessories made from upcycling expired airasia's life jackets.
Enjoy discounts and shop responsibly on any of the Destination GOOD ’s products like @airasiagood’s exclusive Soggy No-More bags via airasia ride! 🚗 https://t.co/hcQwACfeeV
